All the feels today — Liliana finished up her second year of preschool today and will be moving to a different school that’s closer to our house starting next year. Liliana started at this school in the fall of 2021 with an IEP — she was a 3-year-old girl who could barely string 2 words together and had major speech delays. Thanks in large part to some wonderful staff who genuinely cared for Liliana so much — specifically her teacher and speech therapist at the school — she has made tremendous growth in her speech and truly is one of the most social kids you’ll ever meet. She even got the “Storyteller Award” at school today. 😂 We’re so proud of you, Liliana. 💕
